  "title": "MARKETING CUM ADMIN ASSISTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Create and edit marketing materials, including\nsocial media posts, email newsletters, blog posts, and flyers</li></ul><ul><li>Assist in planning, implementing, and monitoring\nmarketing campaigns across digital and traditional channels</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor social media platforms, post content,\nand engage with followers</li></ul><ul><li>Collect data, analyze buying trends, and\ngenerate reports on marketing performance</li></ul><ul><li>Manage marketing calendars, organize files and\ncoordinate with vendors or external agencies</li></ul><ul><li>Assist with the planning and execution of\npromotional events, trade shows, and webinars</li></ul><ul><li>Support HR</li></ul><ul><li>Maintain accurate records and databases</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure confidentiality of company information</li></ul><ul><li>Assist on any ad-hoc given by supervisor</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements & Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Fresh Entry, Diploma or equivalent qualification</li></ul><ul><li>Requires to work in the evenings/weekends for Events/Roadshows</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel,\nPowerPoint)</li></ul><ul><li>Good written and verbal communication skills</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a\nteam</li></ul><ul><li>Training will be provided</li></ul>",
